><path d="M7.521 2.302c.154-.311.23-.467.335-.516a.33.33 0 0 1 .287 0c.104.05.181.205.335.516l1.458 2.954a.7.7 0 0 0 .1.173q.046.048.105.075c.044.021.094.028.196.043l3.26.477c.344.05.516.075.595.159.07.073.102.173.089.273-.015.114-.14.236-.388.478L11.534 9.23a.7.7 0 0 0-.134.15.3.3 0 0 0-.04.122c-.006.049.003.1.02.2l.557 3.245c.059.342.088.513.033.615a.33.33 0 0 1-.232.169c-.114.02-.268-.06-.575-.222l-2.915-1.533a.7.7 0 0 0-.184-.08.3.3 0 0 0-.128 0 .7.7 0 0 0-.185.08L4.836 13.51c-.307.162-.46.243-.574.222a.33.33 0 0 1-.232-.169c-.056-.102-.026-.273.032-.615l.557-3.245c.017-.1.026-.151.02-.2a.3.3 0 0 0-.04-.122.7.7 0 0 0-.134-.15L2.107 6.934c-.249-.242-.373-.364-.388-.478-.013-.1.019-.2.088-.273.08-.084.251-.109.595-.16l3.26-.476a.7.7 0 0 0 .197-.042.3.3 0 0 0 .103-.076c.034-.036.056-.082.102-.173z"stroke=#F8C663 stroke-linecap=round stroke-linejoin=round stroke-width=1.5 /></svg><svg fill=none height=16 width=16 xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg><path d="M7.521 2.302c.154-.311.23-.467.335-.516a.33.33 0 0 1 .287 0c.104.05.181.205.335.516l1.458 2.954a.7.7 0 0 0 .1.173q.046.048.105.075c.044.021.094.028.196.043l3.26.477c.344.05.516.075.595.159.07.073.102.173.089.273-.015.114-.14.236-.388.478L11.534 9.23a.7.7 0 0 0-.134.15.3.3 0 0 0-.04.122c-.006.049.003.1.02.2l.557 3.245c.059.342.088.513.033.615a.33.33 0 0 1-.232.169c-.114.02-.268-.06-.575-.222l-2.915-1.533a.7.7 0 0 0-.184-.08.3.3 0 0 0-.128 0 .7.7 0 0 0-.185.08L4.836 13.51c-.307.162-.46.243-.574.222a.33.33 0 0 1-.232-.169c-.056-.102-.026-.273.032-.615l.557-3.245c.017-.1.026-.151.02-.2a.3.3 0 0 0-.04-.122.7.7 0 0 0-.134-.15L2.107 6.934c-.249-.242-.373-.364-.388-.478-.013-.1.019-.2.088-.273.08-.084.251-.109.595-.16l3.26-.476a.7.7 0 0 0 .197-.042.3.3 0 0 0 .103-.076c.034-.036.056-.082.102-.173z"stroke=#F8C663 stroke-linecap=round stroke-linejoin=round stroke-width=1.5 /></svg></div> <p class="body_l_500 review_text">“Everything works as it should - no glitches, normal speed, decent functionality, no issues. They operate transparently, always open to communication - any question can be resolved. I've been using it for quite a while and don't plan to leave.”</p> <div class="body_l_500 reviewer_wrapper"><div class=reviewer><p class=reviewer_name>Berty Maer<p class="body_s reviewer_data">Latvia</div><div class="body_l_500 custom-pagination"data-review-pagination>1 / 3</div></div></ul></div></div></div></section><section class="section faq"><div class="container faq"><div class=faq_title_wrapper><h2 class="section-title faq h1">FAQs</h2><p class="faq__subtitle body_l">Got Questions? We've Got Answers!</div><div class=faq__list_wrapper><div class=faq__list data-faq-wrapper><div class=faq__column><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">What types of memory and processors do your servers use, and at what frequencies?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>On virtual hosting processor 2 x Intel Xeon E5-2630v3 RAM 256 GB DDR4 ECC. Virtual private servers use Intel Xeon processors of different models from the latest v3-v5 lines with a core frequency of 2400 MHz. RAM is mostly used - DDR-3. HP Proliant G9 dedicated servers have DDR-4 and processors: Intel Xeon Silver 4116, 2xIntel E5-2430v2, Intel E5-2650v2, 2xAMD EPYC 7402, 2xAMD EPYC 7702, 2xIntel E5-2630v4, Intel Xeon Gold 6134, 2xIntel Xeon Gold 6134. For cloud VPS - HP Generation G10 servers with powerful Intel Xeon Gold 6148 processors. Core clock frequency 2.4-3.70 GHz, 20 cores, 40 threads.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">When will the service or server be issued?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>The service will be issued within a few seconds to 30 minutes. When you rent a dedicated server, it will be issued within a few hours to 5 business days, depending on equipment availability. Depending on the OS, the cloud VPS activation process usually takes a few minutes. Activation time can vary depending on your chosen operating system and any customizations you request. Linux deploys in 1 minute. Windows deploys in 2 minutes. Installing the OS from your image may take longer.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">What payment methods do you accept?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>At the moment, the following payment methods are available: -Stripe: Payment by bank cards, including VISA, MasterCard, and American Express. -PayPal -Coinify: We accept BTS cryptocurrency and alternative cryptocurrencies. -Methods of payment with us may vary from country to country. If you haven’t found a convenient way to pay, write to us in chat, and we will advise you further.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">How can I determine the best hosting plan?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>To choose a suitable hosting tariff, virtual server rental, or dedicated server, you need to analyze the needs of your project and future plans. Determine yourself or check with developers what resources (CPU, RAM, disk space, bandwidth) are required. Take into account current needs and possible future growth. If you are in doubt, we can advise you in our online chat or in a ticket.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">What control panels do you use?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>CPanel is preinstalled on virtual hosting. You can install any desired OS or server control panel on virtual servers. We support the following panels: VestaCP, ISPManager, and CPanel.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">How do I receive a refund for a service if I no longer need it?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>If you no longer require the service, please contact our customer service department, and we will return the balance of unused funds to your account.</div></div><div class=faq__column><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">How quickly can I receive a response from your technical support team?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>Our technical support team works 24/7, 365 days a year. Response times to a request range from 5 to 30 minutes.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">How can I upgrade my Shared Hosting and/or virtual server services?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>If you have purchased a shared hosting service but are in the process of development or improvements and see that you need more than the resources, you just need to choose a higher tariff in your personal cabinet. Don’t worry; the tariff will expand while preserving all data and recalculating the paid period. If you need another tariff for a VPS server or dedicated server, you can migrate to a more productive server or add RAM/memory by contacting our tech support.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">What are your NS servers?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>Our NSs: ns1.zomro.net ns2.zomro.ru ns3.zomro.com ns4.zomro.su</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">Do you offer unlimited traffic, and what is the channel's bandwidth?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>Traffic on shared hosting and virtual servers is unlimited. Channel bandwidth on virtual servers from 250 to 500 Mbit/s. With the exception of dedicated servers, where the bandwidth channel is from 100Mbps to 10Gbps. The price of each cloud server includes a paid amount of Internet traffic. There are no traffic restrictions, and additional funds will be charged only for traffic overruns. Channel bandwidth on cloud servers is 1000Mbps.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">Do you have free SSL?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>Yes. You can install the free SSL, Let's Encrypt. If you have any difficulties, you can always contact our technical support.</div><div class="faq__list-item border_gradient"data-btn-plus data-faq-item data-showmore-btn><h3 class="faq__question h6">How reliable is your network and equipment?</h3><button aria-label="plus icon"class=faq__btn-plus type=button><div class=faq__plus-icon></div></button><p class="faq__answear body_s"data-faq-answear>Our network is of premium quality because we use only the most modern network equipment. It protects against DDoS attacks. In addition, there is a vast network capacity with all major TIER-I transit providers. Our servers are located in TIER-III level data centers.</div></div></div><button class=faq__showMore_wrapper data-show-more-faq type=button><div class=faq__show_more data-show-more-text>Show more</div> <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16"class=faq_shevron fill=none height=16 width=16 xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg><path d="m3.918 5.752 4.496 4.496 4.496-4.496"stroke=currentColor stroke-linecap=round stroke-width=1.2 /></svg></button></div><img alt=faq_sphere class=faq_sphere loading=lazy src=/static/site/imagesNew/faq_sphere.avif?v=1760077490></div></section></div></main><script defer src=/static/site/build/js/main_bundle.js?v=1760077490></script><footer class=footer><div class=container><div class=footer__main-wrapper><div class=footer__logo_wrapper><a aria-label="Go to the main page"class="header__main_link logo-link"href=https://zomro.com/> <svg viewbox="0 0 140 40"class=header__logo_icon fill=none height=40 width=140><path d="M18.17 25.289c-3.994-2.281-5.362-7.333-3.057-11.283s7.413-5.304 11.406-3.023"stroke=url(#logo_svg__a) stroke-linecap=round stroke-width=1.162 /><path d="M16.05 28.879c-5.986-3.418-8.036-10.989-4.581-16.907 3.456-5.92 11.108-7.95 17.093-4.531"stroke=url(#logo_svg__b) stroke-linecap=round stroke-width=1.162 /><path d="M13.734 31.798C5.904 27.326 3.22 17.421 7.741 9.676 12.262 1.929 22.276-.725 30.108 3.747"stroke=url(#logo_svg__c) stroke-linecap=round stroke-width=.775 /><path d="M19.922 6.983c.703 0 1.273-.564 1.273-1.26 0-.695-.57-1.259-1.273-1.259-.704 0-1.274.564-1.274 1.26 0 .695.57 1.259 1.274 1.259Z"fill=#561F4F stroke=#F7579F stroke-width=.775 /><path d="M11.435 25.45c.703 0 1.273-.563 1.273-1.258s-.57-1.26-1.273-1.26-1.273.564-1.273 1.26c0 .695.57 1.259 1.273 1.259Z"fill=#561F4F stroke=#C631BC stroke-width=.